lines.text: his voice is strong and clear
it's a dark and smoky place
so you can't quite see his face
he was born into some money
and he knows a thing or two
about the things that you should do
hang out a lot with hemingway
with archie moore and sugar ray
at the rumble in the jungle
with hunter s. and jackie o.
and when they shoot poor bobby down
you wrestle sirhan to the ground
and miss them when they go
you should write a book or two
even if it never makes a dime
by your feet above the circus ring
and space to do it all
drink a cocktail wear a tie
if you don't set it free

paragraphs.text: there's a tall thin man standing in the shadows when he calls your name his voice is strong and clear it's a dark and smoky place so you can't quite see his face he pulls you close and whispers in your ear
and he tells you he was born into some money but it didn't mean he had to sit around and he knows a thing or two about the things that you should do if you don't want to take life lying down
first of all hang out a lot with hemingway spend some time fighting bulls in spain you should go three rounds with archie moore and sugar ray so damn scary you won't mind the pain
be ringside at the rumble in the jungle make friends with hunter s. and jackie o. and when they shoot poor bobby down you wrestle sirhan to the ground love your friends and miss them when they go
you should write a book or two and start a magazine even if it never makes a dime you should swing out by your feet above the circus ring at the very least throw parties all the time
time and tide will never care not so far from here to there we just go
so enjoy yourself do the things that matter cause there isn't time and space to do it all love the things you try drink a cocktail wear a tie show a little grace if you should fall
don't live another day unless you make it count there's someone else that you're supposed to be something deep inside of you that still wants out and shame on you if you don't set it free
